HEADWORD: Weather-bound
<hw>Weath"er-bound`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Kept in port
or at anchor by storms; delayed by bad weather; <as>as, a
<ex>weather-bound</ex> vessel</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Weathercock</ent>⟦br⟧
